Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.31,0:01:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,long time since we've been here and this is like a whole home week here and we\Nwere in snow for you we thought that would be nice create a creative life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.68,0:01:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,actually rains the snow and we want to thank them for it yes thank you for the\Nsnow sweetheart we we she said she had a surprise for us and so don't even do
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.90,0:01:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,things like that elsewhere in the world you're stuck with the weather here we\Njust create it whatever suits us what happened to the music anyway the magic
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.68,0:02:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,music well and to celebrate today we we heard from a publisher in Russia we're\Ngonna be in Russian now so like
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.10,0:02:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're in Russian we're in Slavovian we're in Slovenian we're in all different\Nlanguages so that's very nice and I brought my ego with me
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.09,0:04:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to see if it was working well let's see I forgot about what\Ntoday's lecture is about does anybody know illuminating thought alright last one yes retry
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.93,0:04:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was in the laboratory uh and I remember there was this seminar this guy was so interested in\NCommunity Studies very similar to what Mr. Bogen doesn't like and I mean really knows everything
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.12,0:04:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,he's into He knows where his boy gets whatever he has to hide what he has to hide here so so i don't\NOh oh she does this investors an investigation not on my existing circuitry one before we know what a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.40,0:04:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of these protocols go I guess was so Daar ratio where people think i'm not even an artist I'm an instructor\NI don't have any thoughts about the lecture today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.57,0:04:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll have to wing it.\NWell, since we last were here, we've been all around the country and talked here and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.42,0:04:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've discovered that it's better to start the lecture from the end and work back to the front.\NSo we'll start with the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.21,0:05:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That way you don't have to listen to the rest.\NToday has to do with, I believe, transcending thought. Isn't that what it's about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.59,0:05:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with a condition that is already in existence\Nand how to just become aware that it's already there and that you don't have to do anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.34,0:05:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You can save many lifetimes by just getting a simple understanding of how things come about in the world, you see.\NAnd it'll save you all kinds of worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.75,0:05:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because\Na group like this, which calibrates quite high,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.28,0:05:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the obstruction to enlightenment is really the intellect.\NFor 85% of the population on the planet today,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.73,0:06:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the problem is really to cross over 200 to become oriented and to value integrity, truth, and honesty.\NAnd in America now, 51% of the people calibrate over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.37,0:06:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In 4090,\N15% are trudging along.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.51,0:06:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And we hope to inspire them to move faster.\NSo in a group like this, which has already decided that they'll give up murder and robbery and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.82,0:06:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and thievery is a lifestyle,\Ngive up recidivism and live in the world instead of a prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.16,0:06:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,um,\Num,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.55,0:06:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the problem is, therefore, the mind.\NSo, you see, each level on the scale, I've got a new pointer thing, but I don't know where it is here, someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.84,0:07:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Someplace, it's in my, somewhere, anyway.\NAnyway, we, we, oh, there it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.40,0:07:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so new, I don't even know I have it.\NLook at there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.02,0:07:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ta-da!\NLet's see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.32,0:07:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The world, uh, you know, the world over time, you know.\NTo understand the ego is to not be at the effect of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.96,0:07:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that it's a development that occurred over great eons of time.\NAnd we have a slide on the eons of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.12,0:07:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Over great millennia, then life appeared at consciousness level one, as bacteria,\Nuh,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.60,0:08:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Algae and viruses don't have any consciousness.\NDon't ask me why. Apparently they don't think about anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.00,0:08:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't until you get to a bacteria that you start to worry.\NBacteria, Calvary said, won. We'll get to that slide later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.03,0:08:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, great millennia, on through the animal kingdom, on up through the Komodo dragon,\Nand that's level Bin Laden.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.05,0:08:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he calibrates the same.\NUp through the reptiles, and then we get to domestic animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.05,0:08:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally we get to the capacity over 200 herbivores.\NThe grass eaters calibrate about 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.14,0:08:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you get on to the scale of consciousness.\NSo we see that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.46,0:08:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nconsciousness of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.78,0:09:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Neanderthal man, about 75 here.\NNeanderthal man really wasn't man, he was pre-man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.39,0:09:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Neanderthal didn't evolve into Homo erectus or Homo sapien.\NHe got off the train there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.39,0:09:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Being smart.\NHe got off. And he disappeared into oblivion and reemerged then later.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.52,0:09:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Off the evolutionary tree is Homo erectus\Nand Homo erectus and 600,000 years ago finally Homo sapiens,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.52,0:09:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Idelta, appeared in Ethiopia.\NAt about this consciousness level here, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.89,0:09:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it took many, many centuries.\NAt the time of Buddha, the consciousness level of man was 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.47,0:10:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time of Jesus Christ, the consciousness level of mankind was 100.\NWhen you look at the teachings of the ancient masters,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.64,0:10:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to realize to whom they were talking.\NTo whom they were talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.64,0:10:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, over a great millennia of time, it got up to 190.\NIt stayed at 190, below the level of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.64,0:10:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And then recently, in the late 80s, crossed over.\NAnd now, when we were in San Francisco,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.02,0:10:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,right during the session, at the end of the session,\Nit went from 205 to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.02,0:10:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the time of the last,\Nyou know, harmonic concordance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.40,0:10:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And we happened to be talking to a large group in San Francisco,\Nand we calibrated the level of consciousness at 515.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.40,0:10:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was supposed to happen from 518 to 530,\NSan Francisco time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.72,0:10:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And in front of a whole audience, and it's on video,\Nwe did the calibrated level of mankind at quarter after five.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.72,0:11:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we all did OM,\Nand other wondrous things, and prayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.92,0:11:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And by God, at 530,\Nconsciousness level jumped from 205 to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.01,0:11:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have a new millennia in which we're living.\NAt 207, non-integrity tends to surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.11,0:11:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, at 190, it's just everybody does business that way.\NA few bucks under the table,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.14,0:11:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a little wink here, a little wink there.\NThe old boy network,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.68,0:11:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which, as Wall Street has found out,\Nisn't working out anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.68,0:11:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The old boy network doesn't work anymore.\NAnd interestingly enough, along with the old boy network,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.75,0:11:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that the women CEOs,\Nthe companies run by women CEOs,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.64,0:11:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,according to Fortune magazine,\Nwere more profitable than the corporations run by men.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.64,0:12:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Considerably more, in fact.\NLike 30% more profitable than the ones run by men.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.25,0:12:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.84,0:12:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, women are making tremendous executives.\NI was saying to myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.84,0:12:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,now why is that?\NWell, I saw it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.84,0:12:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because men come from a different culture,\Nin which the old boy network,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.84,0:12:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you do me a favor, I do you a favor.\NYou know, many years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.84,0:12:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody offered me an insider,\Nit would get you prosecuted nowadays,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.84,0:12:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever you call it.\NAnyway, he ran the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.20,0:12:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he said, give me 10,000\Nand I'll give you 100,000 back in a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.20,0:12:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I didn't do it,\Nbut probably because I didn't have 10,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.83,0:12:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, actually, by that time,\Nintegrity, it would create guilt, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.86,0:12:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, in the old boy network,\Nthen, amongst men,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.86,0:13:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,certain deviations from\Nabsolute purity have been part of the culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.86,0:13:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not part of the women's culture.\NNot part of the women's culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.86,0:13:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And when women first appeared as CEOs,\Nthe guys all thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.86,0:13:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,boy, they're really picky uni,\Nyou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.86,0:13:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Really picky uni people, you know.\NWell, they're new at the job,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll learn.\NNo, women don't come from that culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.53,0:13:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not from the old boy culture.\NSo, they toe the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.95,0:13:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And I predict, you know,\Nin a few generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.95,0:13:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll be the old girl culture.\NLet me see somebody off your board
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.59,0:13:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll see to it that\Nthings go your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.59,0:13:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But they haven't learned that yet, so.\NI just think that's very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.39,0:13:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I find a lot of women don't know that,\Nso I thought they should know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.39,0:14:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That isn't what we're talking about today, anyway, but.\NSpirituality, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.56,0:14:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually a way of being in the world.\NIt's the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.43,0:14:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not spiritual practices.\NIt's not specific techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.65,0:14:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not sitting in weird positions\Nand breathing in strange ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.88,0:14:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not getting your aura read.\NYour cards told,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.17,0:14:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,your ruins thrown,\Nyour marbles, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.47,0:14:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,New Ageism won't get you there.\NIt will get you in latent,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.47,0:14:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but it will satisfy your curiosity.\NIt's possible to get involved
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.92,0:14:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and then become uninvolved, unscathed,\Nbut it's unlikely.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.20,0:14:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because usually some of it sticks to you.\NAnd I advise people to avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.65,0:15:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause there's hidden energies,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.65,0:15:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the likes of which you're unaware of.\NPeople are naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.72,0:15:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the downside of,\Nthe downside of the human condition
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.72,0:15:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is really not evil.\NIt's not really even ignorant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.72,0:15:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's naivete.\NIt doesn't know any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.72,0:15:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's attracted by the lure of the unusual,\Nthe unique,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.13,0:15:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the odd,\Nthe bizarre.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.13,0:15:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Bamba Rumba\Ngiving you instructions from the other side,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.64,0:15:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera.\NGod help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.65,0:15:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.80,0:15:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness then evolves up to the point\Nwhere integrity now is the rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.96,0:15:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single newspaper,\NI've read for weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.96,0:15:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,has had the impact of that.\NEvery single newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.96,0:16:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly something that's been getting away with something\Nfor a long, long time
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.96,0:16:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is suddenly under the spotlight.\NIt's not a good time
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.18,0:16:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to pull fast ones in the business world.\NWhat was it yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.18,0:16:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday the president of Smith & Wesson\Ngets knocked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.98,0:16:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He really has a criminal record.\NAnd he didn't think it was important
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.98,0:16:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell anybody about that.\NOf course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.32,0:16:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,17 years in prison,\Nthat's not important.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.28,0:16:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree with him.\NI agree that he's turned a corner
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.28,0:16:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and has become an okay person.\NAnd I really don't doubt his integrity nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.28,0:16:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,However,\Nthe fact that he didn't reveal it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.37,0:16:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,put his company at great risk.\NHe and his company should have known better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.56,0:16:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If they don't get a background check on executives\Nbefore they get big salaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.56,0:16:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,they need to be examined.\NSo the board of directors is also careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.66,0:16:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because integrity means\Nthat you also demand integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.92,0:17:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's your style of life.\NSo that's the new lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.17,0:17:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single day there's been\Na scandal of dereliction
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.17,0:17:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from the level of integrity,\Nwhich did not happen in the old days.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.17,0:17:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In the old days,\Nthere weren't big scandals,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.17,0:17:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,much less every day,\Nmuch less in the headlines,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.17,0:17:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,much less celebrities.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.61,0:17:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So today has to do with thought.\NIt has to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.18,0:17:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,transcending thought.\NThe transcendence of thought
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.38,0:17:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is automatic.\NIt's not something you have to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.96,0:17:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,acquire.\NIt's not a discipline.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.28,0:17:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes from a way of contextualizing yourself\Nand contextualizing life
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.82,0:17:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you become\Nthat which is thoughtless.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.04,0:18:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You become that which is thoughtless\Nby virtue of how you contextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.04,0:18:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the meaning of your life\Nand the meaning of life altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.46,0:18:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does the mind think at all?\NWhy does the mind think at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.03,0:18:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Good question.\NThe mind really thinks because of anxiety
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.28,0:18:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and because of safety.\NIt really thinks because of survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.28,0:18:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to do with this thing\Nin the meantime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.43,0:18:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I guess you hold it.\NOkay, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.65,0:18:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I never know what the body's doing.\NIt's saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.65,0:18:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,what do I do with this thing?\NI don't know what to do with this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.65,0:18:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have to think about it.\NThat's why people around are very useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.83,0:18:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You say,\Nwhat is that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.83,0:18:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You say,\Nyou hit that and you get a spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.83,0:18:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I say,\Nwhoa, that's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.83,0:19:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,\Nyou don't really have to know anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.71,0:19:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody around knows\Nand as long as somebody knows,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.71,0:19:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it's fine.\NOnce you understand the reality
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.18,0:19:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own existence,\Nthought comes to a slow intermittency
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.50,0:19:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of a continuous process\Nthat's torture.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.59,0:19:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There's really no necessity\Nto think about anything
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.59,0:19:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,once you understand who you are\Nand what life is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.59,0:19:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What does the mind usually do?\NIt thinks about the future
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.50,0:19:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and it thinks about the past.\NIt ruminates about the past
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.01,0:19:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is the past?\NWell, if the ego is determining
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.56,0:19:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,your perception now,\Nit did also in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.16,0:19:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't remember reality\Nin the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.36,0:20:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only remember\Nthe ego's perceptions
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.55,0:20:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,which are all distorted and BS.\NSo there's nothing in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.71,0:20:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that's real.\NAnd as much as it's not real,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.74,0:20:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no point in ruminating\Nand trying to correct it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.74,0:20:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I'd said that.\NI wish I'd done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.93,0:20:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to handle the past\Nwas well expressed by Bill Wilson
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.93,0:20:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,who was the founder of AA,\Nwho had an enlightening experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.03,0:20:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,was transformed,\Na good part of society
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.03,0:20:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and introduced\Nand made us realize
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.03,0:20:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the healing power\Nof spiritual concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.03,0:20:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill said,\Nthere's only one thing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.99,0:20:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you gotta do about the past,\Nhave a decent regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.17,0:20:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a decent regret\Nand live differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.17,0:20:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,End of story.\NIs that agreeable to everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.65,0:20:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A decent regret.\NLet's say if you were God,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.80,0:20:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what would you say to a person?\NYou killed all those people, man,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.80,0:20:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and you slaughtered all them people.\NAre you sorry?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.80,0:21:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.\NI am.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.93,0:21:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're forgiven.\NIf he's not sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.44,0:21:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you send him back to light world\Nand let him live it all over again
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.44,0:21:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,until he's sorry.\NThen he comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.92,0:21:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You just stay there until you're sorry.\NIsn't that what it's all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.23,0:21:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've realized\Nthat you're sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.23,0:21:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for what happened in the past\Nand you're gonna accept
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.23,0:21:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,a new way of living,\Nwhat more is there to life?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.23,0:21:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there's the future.\NUh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.35,0:21:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We just took care of the past.\NAll your memories of the past
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.40,0:21:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,are distorted perceptions\Nbecause if you went through the past
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.11,0:22:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in an enlightened state,\Nyou wouldn't remember anything about it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.17,0:22:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because nothing happens.\NNothing to recall
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.17,0:22:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,except projections.\NWhen you see they're all projections,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.65,0:22:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they lose their lure.\NWhat about the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.90,0:22:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the future has to do with anxiety.\NIt has to do with planning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.32,0:22:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with anticipated disasters\Nand misfortunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.32,0:22:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we run out of gas\Non the highway, et cetera?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.92,0:22:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What if the world's gonna be hit by a meteor?\NThere's always somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.92,0:22:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,predicting the end of the world.\NThink of all the fortunes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.95,0:22:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that have been made\Nby various people
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.95,0:22:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,predicting the end of the world.\NThere's always a new book.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.24,0:22:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It usually comes out\Nof some mystical thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.24,0:22:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,like you count the number of\Nwhiskers in a seal's mustache,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.43,0:22:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and you multiply that\Nby the stones in the pyramid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.43,0:22:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You divide that\Nby the number of chapters
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.43,0:22:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of books in the Bible.\NYou multiply that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.43,0:23:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,by a sacred number,\Nand you come up with 5082.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.43,0:23:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, man,\Nwe'll give you a new date.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.49,0:23:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is coming to an end\Nin 5082.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.49,0:23:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How does that affect your life?\NNot at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.64,0:23:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,See, all these books\Nthat predict the end of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.64,0:23:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in thousands of years,\NI don't know why anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.64,0:23:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,wants to buy them.\NYou're not gonna be here,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.64,0:23:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so...\NThey said next week
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.05,0:23:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it'd be worth reading.\NIn Sedona,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.95,0:23:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we've got all kinds\Nof people like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.95,0:23:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one guy,\Nand he has a funny way
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.95,0:23:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of making his hair and all.\NAnd, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.95,0:23:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,every five or ten years,\Nhe's got a new prediction.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.95,0:23:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So then,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.95,0:23:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,if I predict\Nthe world's gonna end
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.95,0:23:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in such and such a year,\Nand it didn't, man,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.95,0:23:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd just fold up my tent.\NI'd just say,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.80,0:23:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,oops,\Nand find something else to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.80,0:23:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NThese people don't even have that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.96,0:23:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.96,0:23:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,they come back next year,\Nthey got a new prediction
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.41,0:24:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that they counted\Nthe ruins
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.41,0:24:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Temple of Karnak wrong,\Nmeasured it in sacred geometry,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.41,0:24:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and came up with 2043.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.48,0:24:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they come back.\NI always tell these people,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.48,0:24:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're gonna predict\Nthe end of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.48,0:24:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,make it far in the future, man,\Nso that when they're all gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.57,0:24:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody will ever know\Nyou're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.57,0:24:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who have\Na decent regret,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.57,0:24:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a really heartfelt regret,\Nare the ones
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.57,0:24:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,who have a decent regret.\NThey're the ones
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.18,0:24:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,who have a decent regret.\NThey're the ones
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.18,0:24:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,who have a heartfelt regret\Nfor human error.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.37,0:24:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,\Nthe human is built,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.37,0:24:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,he's fallible.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.37,0:24:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,errors are certain.\NIf you haven't made
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.37,0:24:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,serious errors in your life,\Nyou're a liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.37,0:24:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,To say you haven't made\Nserious errors in your life
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.37,0:24:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is already a serious error.\NWe've all screwed up mindily,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.37,0:24:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.37,0:24:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.37,0:24:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.37,0:24:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.37,0:24:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.37,0:24:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.47,0:25:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.76,0:25:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.76,0:25:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.76,0:25:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.01,0:25:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.03,0:25:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.38,0:25:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.38,0:25:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.38,0:25:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.38,0:25:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.38,0:25:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.38,0:25:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.38,0:25:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.38,0:25:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.38,0:25:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.38,0:25:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nas Christ said, forgive them for they know not what they do,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.89,0:25:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Buddha said the same thing.\NSo the one sin of the past from which all human beings suffer
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.52,0:25:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is ignorance, not knowing the full truth.\NThis is a condition of all of society, and it doesn't make you special.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.24,0:25:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord, I've sinned.\NPeople make a big drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.93,0:26:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a whole trip about ashes and sackcloth and suffering\Nand self-flagellation and guilt and misery,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.53,0:26:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and these are people that are looking for God at the bottom of the chart.\NShame, guilt, griefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.20,0:26:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, how I have sinned.\NOkay, that gets rid of a little guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.22,0:26:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I'm not going to put it down,\Nexcept after a while you feel guilty that you did that,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.67,0:26:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's beside the point.\NI was looking for God down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.64,0:26:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I heard a lecture that said he was up here,\Nand that changed my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.92,0:26:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NSo everything in the past then is washed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.96,0:27:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to think about the past because there's no reality there.\NIf you were in a state of reality, as I said, there wouldn't be any past.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.70,0:27:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the next thing is fear.\NFear has to do with not realizing that you're safe at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.33,0:27:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the brain and the mind,\Nthey manufacture conditions and take examples from the past
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.23,0:27:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and justify that fear is a rational condition\Nthat you have to think fearfully of the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.52,0:27:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So the future then has to do with control,\Ntrying to control the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.72,0:27:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All this is premised on survival is due to the ego.\NAnd as you get more sophisticated, you realize that,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.71,0:27:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,survival is not a product of the ego.\NIt's a product of the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.87,0:28:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind becomes silent automatically with the realization that you are absolutely safe.\NAnd even if you aren't, so what?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.14,0:28:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So you die.\NDying is a certainty.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.68,0:28:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So accepting the certainty of death, then what can we do about the future?\NYou can be devoted.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.04,0:28:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be devoted to all that is sacred.\NBe devoted to beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.04,0:28:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Be devoted to all that is sacred.\NYou see, the beauty, as we came here this morning, it was stunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.90,0:28:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The only difficulty with beauty is it makes you cry,\Nand you shouldn't be driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.27,0:28:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as you said, what are you crying about this morning?\NHe said, I don't know, it's just the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.39,0:29:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the snow in Sedona, you cry with happiness.\NAnyway, first time we've had it all year.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.09,0:29:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to be aware and to be aligned with, to honor divinity and all of its expressions,\Nto be sensitive to the beauty that exists at every moment in all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.90,0:29:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the spiritual pathway through this world is only a way of being.\NAnd you become that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.96,0:29:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm not crazy about various techniques.\NBreathing and sitting in strange ways and contorting your body and sucking your stomach
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.20,0:30:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's against your spine and weird things.\NIt's only necessary to just be who you really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.97,0:30:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a divine state.\NAnd when walks through the world on the wings of truth, the divine state reveals itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.83,0:30:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When you realize the truth of your own existence.\NSo therefore, how you contextualize your life, then, is how you present yourself to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.02,0:30:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's what you are to the world.\NThe universe responds in like.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.11,0:30:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When you are thus to the world, the world is thus to thee.\NAnd you walk safely through the hail of bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.94,0:30:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And you walk safely through the hail of bullets.\NAnd you walk safely through the hail of bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.10,0:31:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And if one's meant for you, so.\NAnd if you come out the other side, then there wasn't one meant for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.04,0:31:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is the way it goes.\NSo that is complete surrender, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.55,0:31:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The past is eliminated by the realization that a decent regret is all that's necessary.\NLet's make sure about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.15,0:31:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NA decent heartfelt regret does indeed undo the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.94,0:31:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh Lord, amen. Resist.\NIt does indeed undo the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.49,0:31:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In one instant, that's all it takes.\NSo you can stop ruminating and trying to rewrite the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.60,0:31:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lying in bed.\NI should have said this, I shouldn't have said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.62,0:31:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have bought this stock, I should have bought this stock.\NI shouldn't have bought that stock.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.50,0:32:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have.\NSo the past was a learning program.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.68,0:32:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's the point of that learning?\NThe point of that learning is for you to have a decent regret about it and let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.52,0:32:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,To stop dragging it around.\NI don't want to hear other people's chains dragging.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.84,0:32:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They come up after a lecture and they want to give me about,\Noh, I did this and I did that and then she died and I wasn't there
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.88,0:32:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and my mother-in-law was having her gallbladder out.\NBoy, oh boy, I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.37,0:32:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Susie's daughter says, you're the Bill O'Reilly of spirituality.\NI just say to the lady, cut it out, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.58,0:32:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't drag me along with your sad story.\NI don't want to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.86,0:33:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are people who, you see, wallow in the past\Nbecause their ego is sucking the juices out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.86,0:33:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the juices the ego gets out of wallowing in the past,\Nsackcloth and ashes, all the drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.95,0:33:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's drama.\NDrama.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.36,0:33:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Drama.\NYou're also trying to control God and tell him what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.64,0:33:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive you because look how you suffer.\NThat's blackmail.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.91,0:33:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All the people try to blackmail God with suffering.\NYou realize how you're trying?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.39,0:33:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a control thing, isn't it?\NGod is this awful parent and if you just suffer and wallow in guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.37,0:33:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,then he'll forgive you.\NYou don't have to manipulate God because God is a condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.70,0:33:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-manipulable.\NLike a giant electrostatic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.74,0:34:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThat's the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.56,0:34:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The future then is surrendering to the will of God completely with no reservation.\NAnd that's a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.37,0:34:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A way of being in the world.\NAnd it's letting go, wanting to control the world, control the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.33,0:34:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a negative view of yourself, then you expect the worst in the future\Nand you begin to plan for the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.77,0:34:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're extrapolating, you're projecting out there what you think you are.\NDon't think what you are at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.58,0:34:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be what you are and don't think about it.\NHow can you just be what you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.43,0:34:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it in one instant.\NBe willing to accept what I'm saying to you right now with no reservation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.29,0:35:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that easy?\NIf I tell you E equals MC squared, I don't want some smartass to get up there
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.72,0:35:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and start to argue with the mathematics of it.\NI'm telling you E equals MC squared.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.22,0:35:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want some smartass to get up there and start to argue with the mathematics of it.\NI'm telling you E equals MC squared.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.50,0:35:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Get it?\NJesus Christ, that's so simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.46,0:35:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, everybody can see it.\NIt's just matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.07,0:35:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just energy, condensed energy.\NI mean, you don't have to even go to school to figure that one out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.17,0:35:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Once somebody explains it to you.\NSo we accept things on faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.36,0:35:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We accept things on faith.\NTo completely surrender one's will to God, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.29,0:35:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,means whatever happens in the future happens in the future.\NDon't worry about the mind going silent and leaving us stranded.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.32,0:36:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I get letters from like that all the time.\NI'm meditating and my mind stops, and that scares me because how will I survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.70,0:36:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe you won't.\NI don't know what she wants to survive for.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.70,0:36:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She's all the way home.\NWhy not just be there?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.57,0:36:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the kids?\NLet God worry about the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.75,0:36:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the world worry about the kids.\NYes, this week one came that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.52,0:36:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We said, let God worry about the kids.\NIf you bliss out, you bliss out.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.26,0:36:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody blisses out, you sit them down.\NYou put a tin cup next to them, and people walk by.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.26,0:36:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mother-in-law comes and gets the cups.\NEmpties it every hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.73,0:37:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Children are okay.\NDon't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.92,0:37:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So we let go of wanting to change the past, and we let go of wanting to control the future.\NAnd that's done at a profound depth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.59,0:37:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,One realizes that you are safe, not because it says so in a book, but because you realize that.\NAs I stand here, you don't see any past hanging off of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.08,0:37:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You see any past anywhere?\NI don't see any past.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.91,0:37:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When is a karmic product at this moment?\NThat which stands here is where evolution is at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.18,0:37:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThe present is the finish of the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.01,0:38:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,With spiritual realization, which you come by through contemplation, it's really a contemplative matter.\NAs you walk about, you say, who am I to myself anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.13,0:38:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Who am I to the world?\NWhat am I to life?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.44,0:38:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What is my relationship to life?\NWhen you reverence all that is beautiful, when you reverence all that is divine by virtue of its existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.61,0:38:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,then you walk about in a different state.\NOut of that state arises a conviction of safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.15,0:38:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind will start up periodically when it needs to tell you something.\NNot because it's coming from the mind, but because it's coming from the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.70,0:39:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need to know something, the spirit will see to it that you remember to take your vitamins.\NThe ego doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.94,0:39:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes credit for it.\NBut it's really the spirit acting through your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.71,0:39:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Who sees to it that you eat and all those things?\NShe has a big thing about eating, I don't know, every few days I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.74,0:39:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people are concerned about the body.\NIf you're not concerned about the body, other people worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.08,0:39:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need to eat something, somebody will tell you that.\NSo you don't have to think about when will I eat next or what am I going to eat next
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.40,0:39:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's all handled.\NIt's all handled by the nature of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.36,0:40:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want everybody here to feel profoundly safe.\NYou're safe from your past.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.38,0:40:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anybody here who lacks a decent regret for the past?\NI'll help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.44,0:40:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody?\NAnybody who doesn't have a decent regret for the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.33,0:40:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We just confirmed that that's all you need.\NYou don't have to invoke God's mercy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.49,0:40:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to invoke the mercy of an electrostatic condenser.\NWhen you put a charge, it crackles.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.68,0:40:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When there's no charge, it doesn't crackle.\NYou don't say, oh dear electrostatic condenser, give me the presence of thy presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.03,0:40:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The past is over.\NSo you only have to look at the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.72,0:41:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The future you surrender to God\Nso you don't have to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.10,0:41:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That leaves you in the present, whatever that is.\NDoes anybody have any thoughts about the present?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.40,0:41:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to make one up, don't you?\NYou don't really have any thoughts about the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.70,0:41:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so if you give up wallowing in the past\Nand trying to rewrite history and make yourself look better,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.70,0:41:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,cleaner, brighter, and smarter,\Nand if you don't have to worry about your survival in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.92,0:41:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing's going on in the present as you can see,\Ndon't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.30,0:41:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's nothing for the mind to think about.\NThe mind becomes silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.92,0:41:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, the mind doesn't have to become silent.\NThe mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.53,0:42:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing there?\NShading the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.34,0:42:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Shading the screen.\NOh, I see what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.38,0:42:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you were sending me mysterious signals or something.\NDon't think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.49,0:42:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see, when you have to think,\Nall of a sudden a thought comes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.58,0:42:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It says,\Nit's a thought of curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.58,0:42:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What is she doing with that car there?\NSo I don't have to worry that I won't think about things
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.09,0:42:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,when I should think about things.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.18,0:42:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You surrender your thoughts to God\Nbecause they aren't worth anything anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.18,0:42:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,other than E equals MC squared,\Nand you don't know what that means anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.92,0:42:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All I'm saying is we take certain things on faith.\NWe take certain things on faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.14,0:43:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That somebody who has been there\Nwill tell you how it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.53,0:43:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and you just say,\Noh, the big mistake is to argue with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.90,0:43:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Marco Polo went to China, he came back,\Nand I'm sure a lot of people thought he was making up stories,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.18,0:43:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but that was their problem.\NI've been to China,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.07,0:43:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,just the way he said it was.\NThe Chinese are very Chinese-y.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.87,0:43:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I can say.\NThings are, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.87,0:43:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith and confidence, then,\Nin wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.05,0:43:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we're talking about is faith and confidence in wisdom.\NAnd we'll talk about what wisdom is,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.06,0:43:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,how it expresses itself\Nin spiritual teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.06,0:43:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhere were we?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.66,0:43:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about not thinking,\Nwhich leads us in the middle of nowhere, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.66,0:44:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do we go from here?\NHow many people are here for the first time?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.06,0:44:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my gracious me, oh, my, oh, my.\NWell, then we'll have to hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.31,0:44:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOn with the slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.66,0:44:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We're working on a new book,\Nand, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.02,0:44:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and, uh,\Nwell, it's gonna be something.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.85,0:44:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Just trying to decide on a title.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.33,0:44:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, how about that?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.86,0:44:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the map of consciousness is all over the Internet.\NI don't know how to work the Internet, but people do.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.86,0:44:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And they give me all these things.\NSo we're all over the Internet,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.86,0:44:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,all different languages.\NSo whatever we're talking about seems to have
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.98,0:45:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,some general recognition of its essential truth\Nand its usefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.24,0:45:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind has never had any means\Nof discerning truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.24,0:45:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now,\Nthe capacity to discern truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.24,0:45:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is limited to a small percentage of the population.\NThe kinesiologic technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.84,0:45:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,which itself calibrates at 600,\Nand therefore is not explicable in logical terms,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.90,0:45:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it is only useful\Nif, for people whose own consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.21,0:45:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates 200 or over.\NSo that eliminates about 85,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.40,0:45:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,80% of the world, 85% of the world.\NSo, and then the question itself
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.01,0:45:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,has to be integrous as far as motive.\NSo two people who are integrous
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.01,0:45:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,ask an integrous question,\Nand the way they get a correct answer
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.46,0:46:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is because they're dedicated to truth\Nrather than looking for a position.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.46,0:46:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A positionality or a gain.\NMany people usually don't get the right answers
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.65,0:46:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the intention behind it,\Nwhich is rather glaringly obvious very often.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.79,0:46:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to get the correct answer is\Nto say in the name of the highest truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.79,0:46:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest truth,\NI ask, O Lord, is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.79,0:46:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,this or that or the other thing.\NSo then you make a statement,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.23,0:46:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and you ask the person to quickly resist,\Nand as we said
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.30,0:46:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,before, the acupuncture system\Nis very, very rapid.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.48,0:46:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I hold something in mind\Nand press down her arm,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.48,0:46:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a flash down.\NShe's strong right for a moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.48,0:46:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but if I keep pushing,\Nthat moment is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.48,0:46:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So some people wait too long.\NSo when we demonstrate it,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.79,0:46:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you see how quickly we do it.\NWe say we just want to confirm
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.79,0:47:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the validity of this,\Nthat what we just said is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.79,0:47:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to tell her what I'm holding in mind.\NI can say to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.79,0:47:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm holding in mind is true.\NAll right, let's do it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.87,0:47:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding in mind now is true.\NWhat I'm holding now in mind is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.09,0:47:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding now in mind is true.\NShe doesn't know what I was holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.73,0:47:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't know if I'm holding a hippopotamus,\Na zebra.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.27,0:47:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No way of knowing.\NIt's quick and easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.30,0:47:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are adept at it, others are not.\NIt's like riding a bicycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.30,0:47:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are good at it.\NThey get on the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.87,0:47:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like riding a horse.\NI tried riding a horse for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.97,0:47:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I got thrown about 20 times.\NHorses and I didn't get along until just recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.15,0:48:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, horses and I kissed and made up a course.\NThis horse actually was loving.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.60,0:48:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, whoa, a loving horse?\NOne reason I didn't like them,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.89,0:48:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,they never seemed to be loving.\NBut this horse was actually affectionate.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.91,0:48:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, holy cats.\NWe took it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.91,0:48:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a picture of it.\NThis horse actually gave me a kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.91,0:48:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In that instant, horses and myself,\Nnow I have a lovely relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.91,0:48:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't ridden one since.\NMy orthopedist doesn't recommend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.66,0:48:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,One more fall, Doc, and you've had it.\NLet's go on to number two.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.06,0:48:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to quickly run through the slides\Nfor those who haven't been here before.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.06,0:48:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual work.\NI'm putting this in my right-hand pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.87,0:48:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all witness.\NThis is my thingy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.47,0:49:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a mudra.\NIt isn't what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.33,0:49:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't some performance.\NIt's the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.47,0:49:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you are.\NYour life is a presentation to divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.02,0:49:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the best that you can be\Nat the moment that you are what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.50,0:49:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life then is like a mudra.\NYour life is like a sacred gift to the world and to God
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.55,0:49:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are being all that you can be at any given moment.\NThe sacredness of all of life then
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.51,0:49:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,allows you to see the sacredness of your own.\NThat commitment to contextualize that that's why you're here,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.85,0:49:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to be all that you can be at any moment,\Nto realize the divinity of all things,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.85,0:50:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the beauty of all creation,\Nto leave judgment up to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.55,0:50:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,liberates you from thinking this,\Nthe disease called thinking this.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.34,0:50:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, let's go to the next.\NThis was a contribution from Mr. Selinsky
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.37,0:50:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,whose name has been chopped off the bottom.\NHe translated the consciousness levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.62,0:50:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember I said they had to become logarithmic\Nbecause the numbers are so huge, logarithmic.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.94,0:50:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a logarithmic scale.\NAnd we tried to give comparative in microwatts,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.46,0:50:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, just because people are used to such things.\NWe're really talking about a nonlinear domain,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.84,0:50:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but to make it more comprehensible,\Nwe tried to relate it in comparative figures
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.16,0:51:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to like the electromagnetic spectrum.\NNow, in the things we write and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.47,0:51:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,people tend to become literal.\NThey tend to miss the forest for the trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.39,0:51:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't focus on the trees.\NThe things that we're trying to illustrate
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.39,0:51:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is so you get the gist of it.\NThe gist of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.39,0:51:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so what he did was he translated...\NHe's very good at mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.39,0:51:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not very good at mathematics.\NI don't like mathematics, even.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.64,0:51:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate mathematics.\NAll right, because it's so pedestrian.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.47,0:51:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You're limited to trudging through the linear world.\NI mean, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.95,0:51:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're used to living free like a bird\Nin the nonlinear world,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.00,0:51:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a drag to have to figure everything out.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.54,0:52:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, he correlated it in microwatts\Nusing more advanced mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.54,0:52:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The answers we got were using kinesiology,\Nwhich would make any dyed-in-the-wool scientist shudder.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.63,0:52:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where I figure out certain things.\NI say, how much do I owe the government?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.76,0:52:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology.\NThat's the right figure.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.66,0:52:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got employees that never give me a charge card.\NI say, how much do we owe you?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.66,0:52:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we get the right amount.\NI write them a check.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.66,0:52:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's happy.\NNo problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.68,0:52:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so what he found was\Nwhen he really...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.68,0:52:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The mathematics are not on here.\NI don't know what happened to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.68,0:52:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They fall off the bottom here.\NBut the mathematics is quite advanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.68,0:52:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So he calibrated them,\Nand you see the levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.84,0:53:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of form a...\NLook how they go from 100 to 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.86,0:53:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And then suddenly...\NSo you see them and suddenly at 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.86,0:53:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you see it shoot up like this,\Nand then at 600, it reaches almost infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.86,0:53:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go on to the next one.\NI don't know what that means,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.86,0:53:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but I thought it looked earlier.\NHere's where most of mankind is in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.27,0:53:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's his consciousness level.\NWhere are we at?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.27,0:53:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,207, did I say?\N207.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.33,0:53:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the percentage of mankind over here\Nthat is above 207
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.33,0:53:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually quite minimal.\NAnd the great mass of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.65,0:53:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is behind us in the learning curve.\NInstead of good and evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.10,0:53:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in terms of learning curve.\NSo 15% of mankind is above consciousness level 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.15,0:54:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Next slide.\NAnd Karen in our office made these graphics.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.50,0:54:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You get that the 15% is counterbalancing the 85%.\NTheir creativity, their power, their productivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.17,0:54:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the power that counterbalances the world\Nbecause the power of integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.58,0:54:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is far greater than that of non-integrity.\NAlso, now you understand the power of capitalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.34,0:54:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer to Karl Marx,\Nthis is not exploiting this.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.10,0:54:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is holding it up.\NThis is holding it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.29,0:54:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,One brilliant idea creates more capital\Nthan all the banks in the world are holding.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.42,0:55:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas Edison, one thought.\NThink of the giant economic productivity
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.53,0:55:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of one brilliant thought.\NCapital exists in the mind and not in the bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.88,0:55:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One brilliant thought followed up by Antigris.\NThe rest of it is just automatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.14,0:55:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the 15% that holds up the 85%.\NOkay, what's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.14,0:55:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a new thing here called PowerPoint.\NIt's a mysterious new electronic gadget.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.23,0:55:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We used to flip these transparencies around.\NI don't see even the transparency flipper anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.94,0:55:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We're on our own.\NThis is called the PowerPoint thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.90,0:55:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to get into silent mind.\NYou see, you have to understand how the ego works.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.08,0:56:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And one way it works is by duality.\NAnd it sees everything as opposites.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.08,0:56:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't see things as comparisons.\NIt sees them as opposites.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.08,0:56:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NSo in politics, if people would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.21,0:56:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, this is the way I see it\Nand the way I would go,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.21,0:56:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and why I would go that way,\Nyou know, politics would be Antigris.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.21,0:56:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, they think, instead of doing that,\Nthey just hate this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.21,0:56:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Or this one hates this one.\NI would say, you don't have to hate vanilla
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.40,0:56:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because you like chocolate better.\NYou have to just tell people why chocolate is better than vanilla,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.78,0:56:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but you don't have to hate vanilla.\NAll right, so here we have
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.96,0:56:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,people think of heat, hot and cold\Nas opposites, opposites.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.79,0:56:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind thinks dualistically.\NIt sets up a positionality
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.79,0:56:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and then divides everything\Ninto dualistic pairs, polarities.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.79,0:57:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This against that.\NThis against that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.21,0:57:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Not this and that, but this against that.\NSo actually we see there's only one variable.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.30,0:57:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We see with heat, where's my pointer thing?\NI got to really get used to working this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.37,0:57:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see this thing here?\NAll right, there's only one variable.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.59,0:57:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't hot versus cold.\NThere's only heat, the presence of heat
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.59,0:57:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the absence of heat.\NThere's not two opposites of hot and absence of hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.01,0:57:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no such thing.\NThe kinesiologic response then
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.26,0:57:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is like electricity going down a wire.\NThere is no opposite to on.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.74,0:57:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When you turn off electricity,\Nno offness runs down the wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.74,0:57:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either there or it ain't.\NIt's a presence or the absence of a quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.86,0:57:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we have desirability.\NIf you desire something, it's precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.86,0:58:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't desire it, you think it's awful.\NOkay, now PowerPoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.62,0:58:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is another example.\NYou don't have good versus evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.04,0:58:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got desirability.\NAnd the most obvious one to see is light.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.33,0:58:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one quality of light.\NIt's either present or it diminishes and it's absent.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.58,0:58:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The same with truth.\NTruth either prevails
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.58,0:58:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or it becomes muddied and becomes absent.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.00,0:58:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So that takes care of duality.\NThat is to take care of it for everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.00,0:58:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We said in previous lectures\Nthat one can realize
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.72,0:58:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the real way to become silent\Nis to become
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.72,0:58:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the potentiality of that which you are\Nand accept what I tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.72,0:58:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're perfectly safe.\NThe past doesn't mean diddly.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.72,0:59:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The future isn't here.\NAnd in the present, nothing's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.72,0:59:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's another way\Nand that is by reflection, inner reflection.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.60,0:59:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,By inner reflection,\None will begin to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.60,0:59:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that the mind is silent at all times.\NIf the mind were not silent,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.62,0:59:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't know that you were thinking anything\Nbecause it's against the background of silence
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.91,0:59:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that you think you experience a thought.\NThe mind itself then is the field
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.55,0:59:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in which thought occurs.\NIt's the silence,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.87,0:59:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the backdrop of silence.\NAnd we'll explain thoughts a little bit later,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.29,0:59:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but thoughts,\Njust prior to a thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.51,0:59:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is where you'll notice the silence.\NThis silence can be noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.74,1:00:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what you're doing.\NAs I'm talking right now,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.74,1:00:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind is really in a field of silence\Nso that I'm listening to what's being said.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.63,1:00:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't the slightest idea.\NPeople say,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.86,1:00:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,what are you going to talk about?\NHow would I know what I'm going to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.30,1:00:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell us what you're going to talk about.\NThey want three paragraphs
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.40,1:00:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,sent to their church\Nto announce what you're going to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.40,1:00:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How would I know what they're going to talk about?\NI can make a presumption,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.78,1:00:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so I send them some wild thing.\NI don't want to tell them the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.50,1:00:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have the slightest idea.\NI hear it at the same time you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.81,1:00:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's funny.\NI get a kick out of it when it's funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.18,1:00:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes it's a crack up.\NJust the funniest thought comes out of nowhere
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.78,1:01:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and it just cracks me up.\NPeople say you laugh at your own jokes.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.14,1:01:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not my jokes.\NI don't know where they come from.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.81,1:01:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They crack me up.\NIf they were my joke,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.81,1:01:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they wouldn't crack me up.\NNo, they're not my joke.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.00,1:01:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's real so funny.\NAt all times,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.42,1:01:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,even though you're thinking\Nor think you're thinking,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.42,1:01:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind is actually silent.\N98% of the mind is silent
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.71,1:01:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,even when you think you're thinking.\NYou think it's all your mind is thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.09,1:01:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's about 1 or 2%.\N1.85 to 3.6%.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.08,1:01:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I like how obsessive,\Nmake obsessive-impulsive happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.59,1:01:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you said 1.8.\NNo, no, it's 1.92.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.59,1:01:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an itty-bitty part of your mind\Nis what's thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.06,1:02:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about this much of your mind here is thinking.\NThe rest of it is entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.12,1:02:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so if only 1 or 2% of your mind is thinking,\Nthen how does it have so much,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.91,1:02:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,seem to have so much power over you?\NIt doesn't have any power.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.91,1:02:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You give it the power in the secret.\NI'll give you the secret of what the power is.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.91,1:02:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called hypnosis.\NHypnosis.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.36,1:02:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hypnosis.\NI tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.90,1:02:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch my fingers.\NWatch my fingers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.90,1:02:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch my fingers.\NWatch my fingers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.90,1:02:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch my fingers.\NSleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.90,1:02:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace.\NSleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.90,1:02:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace.\NSleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.06,1:02:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up.\NWake up.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.79,1:02:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.79,1:02:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This 1% keeps you seduced.\NIt traps you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.52,1:02:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lure.\NIt's good to be paranoid about your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.26,1:03:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to no good.\NSo long as it's got you boom-boggled,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.69,1:03:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it survives.\NWhen it stops having you entranced
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.69,1:03:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in its hypnotic condition, lure,\Nit stops.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.75,1:03:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So its days are numbered.\NThe mind knows its days are numbered.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.98,1:03:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego knows its days are numbered.\NConsequently, it's frantic to keep you going
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.58,1:03:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,with a new worry, a new anxiety,\Na new guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.58,1:03:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And how does it do it?\NIt izes everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.81,1:03:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It izes everything, I call it,\Nand it seduces you through guilt,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.28,1:03:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,excitement, promise, lascivious images.\NThat sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.34,1:03:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Lascivious images.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.34,1:03:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,MTV.\NThere you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.49,1:03:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's got nothing else to do,\Nyou'll see your mind will resort
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.50,1:04:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to one of the things on the bullet board.\NIt'll politicize everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.82,1:04:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll moralize.\NIsn't that awful?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.89,1:04:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll idealize how things should be.\NIt's going to hypothesize and rewrite history.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.40,1:04:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to romanticize things.\NAnd one of its favorite entertainments
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.66,1:04:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is to criticize.\NWasn't that awful?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.49,1:04:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's drama.\NDramatizes, emotionalizes things.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.68,1:04:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionalizes.\NPeople love to get on TV and blubber.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.58,1:04:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Blubber.\NThey do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.76,1:04:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They emotionalize.\NThey dramatize.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.76,1:04:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And they do that by catastrophizing.\NCatastrophizing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.69,1:04:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you theorize how it should be.\NAnd you rationalize.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.88,1:04:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you fantasize.\NYou infantilize.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.01,1:04:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Intellectualize.\NYou mentalize everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.01,1:05:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You idealize it.\NAnd you glamorize the whole process
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.01,1:05:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, I'm thinking.\NDon't bother me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.01,1:05:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking.\NWe glamorize things.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.31,1:05:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Exaggerate them because we prize them.\NWe like to victimize and demonize things.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.41,1:05:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So the wise give up izing.\NThe mind keeps going.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.54,1:05:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got you hypnotized.\NSo just to know,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.60,1:05:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,98% of your mind is silent.\NThere's only 1 or 2%.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.60,1:05:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no power over you\Nexcept the hypnotic fascination
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.14,1:05:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that you project to it.\NSo we glamorize.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.14,1:05:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Alice Bailey's book on glamor\Nis probably the best one out of that whole series
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.14,1:05:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or one of the greatest.\NAnd it was described by some spiritual teacher
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.40,1:05:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in the celestial realm.\NThe energy of glamor.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.43,1:05:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't exist in the thing itself.\NIt's something we project onto it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.43,1:06:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we glamorize and exaggerate\Nthe importance of our mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.46,1:06:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Make it a wonderful, wonderful thing.\NOur thoughts are really precious.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.01,1:06:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Precious.\NPrecious thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.49,1:06:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go on to the next.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.67,1:06:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind has different styles\Ndepending on what level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.67,1:06:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you're talking about.\NIn a group like this,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.74,1:06:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm is the big barrier.\NFew people escape to level 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.90,1:06:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we say?\NPoint, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.90,1:06:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,4%.\N4% of the population
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.90,1:06:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,ever transcend to level 500.\N4%, huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.96,1:06:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And to level 540, unconditional love,\N0.4%.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.47,1:06:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So why is it so few people\Ntranscend the barrier of the intellect at 500?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.66,1:06:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As we've said,\NEinstein calibrated 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.91,1:07:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Isaac Newton, 499.\NThe great scientific geniuses of all time, 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.39,1:07:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Great books of the Western world\Nrun around the 460s, around there.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.65,1:07:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, 499.\NSo the intellect now, first of all,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.00,1:07:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,brings people up from the bottom.\NSo each level of consciousness, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.00,1:07:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is an improvement over the other.\NTherefore, there's no point of demonizing it
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.00,1:07:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you don't have enough energy to hate,\Nyou're going to lay down there and die.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.35,1:07:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to be in apathy\Nbecause the first rule of the ego is survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.45,1:07:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the levels of consciousness, then,\Nyou transcend one.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.58,1:07:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So each one is not bad.\NIt's not bad in itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.18,1:07:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one is an improvement over the one below it.\NUnless you can get angry,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.25,1:07:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to be in apathy.\NApathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.47,1:07:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why what's going on in Haiti right now\Nis good.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.98,1:08:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause angriness and rebellion
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.16,1:08:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is an improvement over abject dying of poverty and AIDS\Nand just laying there listlessly
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.32,1:08:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,without enough energy to even feed yourself,\Nwhich is what happens at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.32,1:08:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So angriness is a way up over something.\NThen, once you get beyond that,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.32,1:08:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need angriness anymore\Nand you give it up for courage.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.32,1:08:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you give up courage for valor.\NAnd you give up all those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.32,1:08:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So each level serves its purpose biologically,\Nyou might say,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.48,1:08:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and disappears when you've transcended it.\NWhat's happening up there?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.47,1:08:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy...\NMy God.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.94,1:08:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NThat's the Newtonian mind expressing itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.68,1:09:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I hear you.\NThe Newtonian mind, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.62,1:09:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is a tremendous advance.\NTremendous advance.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.62,1:09:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,To be able to think logically,\Nto know the rules of logic.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.62,1:09:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,See,\Nrationality is really a dialectic.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.62,1:09:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Dialectic.\NIn which bringing the question
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.16,1:09:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,gets you voted out\Nof the debating team
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.32,1:09:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's a violation\Nof the dialectic
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.32,1:09:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of logic.\NThe undistributed, middle,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.42,1:09:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,all those kind of things.\NSo logic has certain rules
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.54,1:09:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which are similar to mathematics.\NAnd people fall below
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.54,1:09:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectual integrity.\NSo intellectual integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.54,1:09:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,really begins in the 400s, 410,\Nand then around 460,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.54,1:09:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that's really\Nintellectual integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.86,1:09:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So I know people prefer to hate George Bush,\Nbut I know they hate to hear it,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.44,1:09:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but he does calibrate at 460\Nso he follows what
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.50,1:10:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in his world is logic.\NLogic.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.54,1:10:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It says here, by the oath of office,\NI should do this, he does that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.54,1:10:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's his duty.\NOther people see their mission differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.59,1:10:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But people in the mid-400s\Nconsider their world
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.59,1:10:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to be logical, scientific,\Nprovable,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.59,1:10:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,based on evidence, etc.\NAnd so the Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.88,1:10:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm of reality\Nis orderly and logical
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.88,1:10:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it sees things as separate.\NSpiritually,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.04,1:10:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside it is\Nof Newtonian is it divides
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.04,1:10:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the world into a dualistic\Nof this causing of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.23,1:10:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as you think there's a this causing of that,\Nyou'll be stuck in duality
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.23,1:10:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will think there's a separate\Nego within yourself, separate from God,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.23,1:10:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of this causing of that.\NWe'll have to transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.05,1:11:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that this morning, too.\NQuantum mechanics is then an advance
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.06,1:11:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Newtonian paradigm\Nstill within the linear world
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.06,1:11:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you see\Nthat things are not happening in an orderly fashion.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.06,1:11:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They're unpredictable.\NWhat you're dealing with really is
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.16,1:11:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,likelihoods, but not certainties.\NThe Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.16,1:11:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,promises certainty.\NAnd within certain limitations
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.16,1:11:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it does bring you to certainty.\NHowever,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.02,1:11:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the world we live in\Nis not ruled by Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.02,1:11:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm.\NWe live in a biologically real
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.12,1:11:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,earthly world\Nin which subjectivity
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.12,1:11:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually the\Nmost prominent factor.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.12,1:11:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It is subjectivity that gives\NNewtonian
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.12,1:11:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm\Nits credence.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.44,1:11:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In and of itself it has no credence,\Nbut subjectively we value it
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.44,1:12:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as highly useful.\NQuantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.30,1:12:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we go beyond that. We see that\Nin the world of biology,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.53,1:12:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world in which we exist,\Nsubjectivity of our own existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.53,1:12:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, things are really quite\Ndisorderly, unpredictable.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.53,1:12:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not bound.\NAnd the most important
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.74,1:12:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,thing is the Heisenberg principle.\NThe discovery that
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.74,1:12:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,things change just by sheer observation.\NThe effect of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.74,1:12:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where\NEinstein bucked.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.16,1:12:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein did not want to accept that\Nhe said, I prefer to think there's
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.16,1:12:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,an independent universe out there\Nthat exists independently of human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.31,1:12:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he refuted it.\NSo he stayed at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.60,1:12:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so\Nquantum mechanics says that
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.79,1:12:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't\Npredict the next thing
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.79,1:12:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that will happen with certainty.\NIf there's one digit off
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.79,1:12:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 26th decimal point\Nand you run that through your computer
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.79,1:13:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,enough times, bang, you'll get a response\Nthat's way out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.79,1:13:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,As people break their backs\Nhigh diving discover 13 jumps
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.42,1:13:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,killed on the 14th.\NRight in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.52,1:13:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I've told this story before.\NTwo guys that used to be off
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.62,1:13:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what you would call a drive there\Nback of the Pizza Hut.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.97,1:13:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you had a rattlesnake in your yard\Nhe'd call them up.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.97,1:13:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They would come over for nothing.\NThey would get the rattlesnakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.18,1:13:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And they did this for years.\NAnd one of the guys
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.18,1:13:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,got bitten 19 times.\N19 times.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.60,1:13:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And the 20th time killed him.\N20th time.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.21,1:13:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of all of them\Nyou presume I must now be immune.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.21,1:13:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NHe wasn't immune.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.50,1:13:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.\NThat's why I tell people
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.97,1:14:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to avoid extreme sports unless you're ready to go.\NYou're ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.10,1:14:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough high dives\Nand just as you go off
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.66,1:14:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the diving board\Nyou suddenly remember
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.69,1:14:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you forgot your mother's\Nyou forgot a Mother's Day card
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.69,1:14:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and that split 1 50th of a second\Nbreaks your back.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.07,1:14:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just don't\NI'm not too hot on extreme sports
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.07,1:14:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because I understand quantum mechanics.\NQuantum mechanics says
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.07,1:14:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,if you do it often enough\Nsooner or later it will get you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.33,1:14:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course we know the many sports stars\Nwho push the envelope
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.33,1:14:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and they rack up.\NIt's the fact that they have driven
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.58,1:14:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,400 races\Nsuccessfully
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.68,1:14:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that the 401th kills them.\NIt's because of the success
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.68,1:14:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 400\Nthat the 401 kills them.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.90,1:14:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's enough\Nof the grim side of quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.90,1:15:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,let's go to something happier.\NThese are the enlightening
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.47,1:15:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the scale only goes up to 600\Nand then we calibrated
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.47,1:15:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the higher levels.\NSee because to many people
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.89,1:15:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,God is an imagination\Nthat somebody thought up somewhere
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.89,1:15:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's a big oppressor.\NThe way God is presented
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.89,1:15:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,he is an oppressor from many points\Nof the presentation.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.89,1:15:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of the liberator\Nhe is the great oppressor
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.89,1:15:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the great feared God of judgment day.\NSo we just wanted to calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.89,1:15:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,reality\Nthe verifiability
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.95,1:15:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual realities\Nso with kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.95,1:15:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,then we got\Nthe enlightenment happens at 600
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.95,1:15:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and beyond here\Nthe numbers of people
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.95,1:15:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,are small\Nbut their impact is very often large.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.95,1:15:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness in mankind\Ngoes up to a thousand
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.95,1:15:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and the reason it doesn't go beyond a thousand\Nis because the human nervous system
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.95,1:16:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is not equipped for it.\NUp to about 700 it's blissful
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.27,1:16:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,kundalini energy flows\Nand it's exquisite
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.27,1:16:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,exquisite\Ntakes you right out of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.59,1:16:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and from there on up\Nfrom there on up for some reason
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.46,1:16:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness may continue\Nusually it does not
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.46,1:16:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,most people over 600\Nwill leave the body
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.49,1:16:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,right then\Nyou don't need to stay there
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.62,1:16:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,like a near death experience\Nyou don't have to re-own the body
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.71,1:16:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about 50% won't survive at all\Nthey just let it topple over
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.32,1:16:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but if surrounding conditions\Nmake sure you eat and all that kind of stuff
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.32,1:16:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the body will survive\Nthen it stays where it is
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.32,1:16:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramana Maharishi, Nisargadatta Maharaj\Nall those are calibrated in 700
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.32,1:16:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so up to about here\Nthe condition is
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.32,1:16:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,exquisite\Nand then sometimes it continues on up
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.32,1:17:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it is not exquisite\Nit is extraordinarily painful at times
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.32,1:17:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,excruciatingly painful\Nand the Buddha said that
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.32,1:17:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ striped blood\Nand from there on up
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.32,1:17:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the human nervous system is just not equipped\Nto handle energies
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.32,1:17:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,over 700\Nand to go over that level
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.32,1:17:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,causes a great deal of\Nsuffering, inner suffering
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.58,1:17:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway, gradually the nerves do begin\Nto develop
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.58,1:17:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,greater capacity\Nthey pull in more protein molecules
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.58,1:17:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and they actually do modify\Nbut it takes some years
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.58,1:17:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes some years\Nand the techniques advance
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.58,1:17:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so it is better to not worry about that\Nhere in this realm
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.58,1:17:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it is better to go to some heavenly realm\Nand do that
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.28,1:17:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so then just for fun\Nwe asked what is an archangel
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.28,1:17:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we got 50,000 and up\N50,000 and up, yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.34,1:17:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was in the pits of hell\Nand I asked
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.44,1:18:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is a God\NI prayed to him for help
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.85,1:18:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the pits of hell\Neternal hell
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.91,1:18:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the pits of hell are eternal\Nexperientially eternal
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.91,1:18:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,eternal with no hope\Nthe certainty of no hope
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.64,1:18:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is so profound\Nyou will never
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.12,1:18:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,leave this state ever\Nand you get what ever means
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.12,1:18:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and then dread\Ntakes on a dimension
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.60,1:18:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn't know it could take\Nand out of that
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.08,1:18:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the voice within said\Nif there is a God I ask him for help
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.07,1:18:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and then out of that\Noblivion
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.23,1:18:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and then out of oblivion and nothingness\Nsuddenly the infinite presence
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.23,1:18:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know\Nwhy I got into that anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.24,1:19:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that heaven and hell\Nare then experiential
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.26,1:19:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,while still in a physical body\Npeople worry about it later
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.26,1:19:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it's experiential right here right now\Nby virtue of one's own decisions
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.26,1:19:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,let's move on to the next one\Noh yes
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.26,1:19:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Archangel\Nthat's what started that
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.26,1:19:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I always think some cruising Archangel\Nsome Archangel cruising by
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.26,1:19:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,heard this little\Nflippy thought
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.26,1:19:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is a God I ask him for help\Nand he went hmm
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.26,1:19:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and went on\Nknocked me out of the world for 30 years
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.12,1:19:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,30 years I never said anything\NI was silent within
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.18,1:19:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I left the world and came out here\Nhmm
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.73,1:19:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,never mentioned anything until 1995\Nit just is such a shock
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.18,1:19:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just like pow\Nthe power of it hits you
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.27,1:19:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the mind is knocked silent\Nso the silence of the mind is the automatic consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.27,1:20:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of a automatic consequence\Nof a level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.27,1:20:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which transcends thinkingness\Nin that state
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.27,1:20:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,there is nothing to think\Nthere is no person to think
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.66,1:20:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no somebody to think\Nbecause somebody-ness is left
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.75,1:20:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no person to think\Nthere is no this to think about
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.90,1:20:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,or that\Nso thinkingness is not
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.90,1:20:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,part of that state\Nthrough witnessing then
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.51,1:20:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we begin to see\Nthe mind looks at form
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.51,1:20:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it registers form\Nit recognizes it
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.51,1:20:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and some spiritual teachers say\Nidentify with this here the watcher
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.51,1:20:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer and the witness\Ninstead of being part of the content of the mind
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.51,1:20:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,merely witness it\Nwe'll move to the next exciting slide
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.15,1:20:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll move to the next\Nexciting slide
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.15,1:21:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,what\Nthe maps
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.99,1:21:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,oh yeah we'll do everything\Nthis is our home team here
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.14,1:21:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,did the maps come up next\Noh yes well this is quite
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.21,1:21:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you know we predicted Haiti\Na couple of years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.21,1:21:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we said here's North America\Nthe calibrated levels
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.43,1:21:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness\NI think there's group karma
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.69,1:21:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,there's group karma\Nyou belong to a group
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.01,1:21:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of your level of consciousness\Nbecause you're ascribed to that
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.58,1:21:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,then that group comes on the planet\Ntends to be in certain areas on the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.26,1:21:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,does what it does\Neither improves its karmic potential
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.26,1:21:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or makes it worse\Nthen we tend to come back again
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.26,1:21:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in karmic groups\Nlet's see if that's so
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.58,1:22:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest good\Nwe have to be a person
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.58,1:22:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,there is like group karma\Nwhat we're seeing
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.58,1:22:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,right in Haiti now\Nis like group karma
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.58,1:22:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,all the great tragedies on mankind\Nhere you've got the western hemisphere
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.58,1:22:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you see Greenland\N345, America
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.58,1:22:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Canada 410, 420\NCentral America in the 300s
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.58,1:22:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not going to get any trouble\Nfrom the whole western hemisphere here
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.61,1:22:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,they're in the high 200s, they're all over 200\Nright in the middle of it
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.61,1:22:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to turn this thing on here\Nthere
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.61,1:22:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we said wow like a big boil\Non your leg
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.95,1:22:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,here's trouble\Nyou've got a 55 in the middle of the 300s
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.95,1:22:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and the 400s\Nwe said that a year or two ago
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.49,1:22:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,55 then\Nso this is some karmic group
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.49,1:22:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes on this way\Nand they've got to evolve beyond it
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.94,1:23:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,what can we do to help Haiti\Nwell I think
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.35,1:23:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nto try and inspire
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.35,1:23:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,through beauty, through excellence\Nthrough demonstrating compassion
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.42,1:23:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,etc.\Nwe're going to send troops there
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.42,1:23:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what our troops are going to do in Haiti\Nbut they're going to go there I guess
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.15,1:23:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really strange\Nwe let Mexicans cross the border
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.15,1:23:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but you don't let Haitians cross the border\Nif they're trying to swim to safety
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.15,1:23:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,why do we put them back\NI don't know, we do that with Cuba
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.60,1:23:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,there's the peculiarities of politics\Nwhich I understand
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.60,1:23:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't really want to understand them\Nnot bad enough as it is
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.82,1:23:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway so we have our preferences\Nand our favorites
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.82,1:23:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's human nature\Nso right in the middle of all these numbers
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.82,1:23:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got a 55\Nand they stand out so strongly
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.05,1:23:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you know that's got to be some kind of a karmic group\Nand there's certain things about their culture
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.21,1:24:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that would make 55\Nyou would understand why it's 55
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.21,1:24:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been there\Nand there's certain things about their culture
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.21,1:24:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that would pretty much guarantee that\Nok let's go to the next one
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.21,1:24:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,exciting trip around the world\Nwe calibrate all the
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.03,1:24:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,countries in the world\Nall the continents
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.48,1:24:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and we learn a great deal\Nhere's Australia at 410
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.61,1:24:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,here you've got 405\Nhere you've got India at 355
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.61,1:24:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got China at 305\Nyou know China is evolving
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.61,1:24:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,China is really coming out of the\NMarxian collapse
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.61,1:24:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and the mayoism\Nthe collective farms
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.77,1:24:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside of\NKarl Marx calibrated at 130
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.77,1:24:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so the downside of Marxism is\Nis starvation
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.77,1:24:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and revolution and disaster\Nand in the great books of the rest of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.90,1:24:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Marx stands out\Nthey're all in the 400s
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.90,1:25:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and Marx is at 130\Nso if by their fruits you shall know them
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.90,1:25:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't say too much for\NMarxism as a lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.09,1:25:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway we see that China is evolving\Nthey have increasing property rights
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.09,1:25:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,civil rights\Netc
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.09,1:25:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,religion and spirituality is still not\Nwelcomed there
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.09,1:25:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's sort of a threat to the\Nstrict secularism
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.37,1:25:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to get the book Power Versus Force\Npublished in China
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.37,1:25:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I was told you've got to clean God out of the whole thing\Nand divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.40,1:25:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and just express it as energy consciousness\Nenergy
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.40,1:25:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,replace God with higher energy\Nand you can get posed in China
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.40,1:25:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as you've got God in there\Nso they've got a way of
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.69,1:25:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,censoring things\Nyeah but still
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.94,1:25:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,China has come up a long way\Nnow it has a new
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.94,1:25:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,premiere\Nthere was a group we were at in California
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.94,1:26:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,some years ago\Nof course the miracles group
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.98,1:26:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and we decided the group would take on China\Ntake on China as a
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.14,1:26:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,group project\Nsince then China has come up
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.36,1:26:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so I don't want to thank anybody\Nwho's here from California for that miracles group
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.36,1:26:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,if it wasn't for you folks\NChina would still be down
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.36,1:26:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200\Nso the new premiere of China
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.06,1:26:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is moving ahead\Nso you get very interesting theory
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.06,1:26:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,here you have Mongolia up here\Ngreat expanses
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.06,1:26:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,here's where the trouble is\Nwe said North Africa
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.06,1:26:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,North Africa is where the trouble is\Nit's basically a large karmic group
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.06,1:26:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got two countries\None at 190 and one at 192
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.06,1:26:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly warring at each other\Nbut they've been doing that for
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.06,1:26:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple thousand years\Nso I don't know if they're going to
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.06,1:26:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,decide to stop or not\Nbut anyway they get too much out of it
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.06,1:26:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole country is built on\Nbuilt on the structure
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.06,1:27:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of strife and conflict\Nand hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.22,1:27:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and we blow up a busload of children\Nand they bomb our school
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.22,1:27:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and the police\Nand they send a rocket
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.73,1:27:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's a whole lifestyle\Nif they wanted to stop it
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.82,1:27:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,they would\Npeople tell you one thing
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.11,1:27:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but if that was so\Nit would be so
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.11,1:27:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's not so\Nand we get to this
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.37,1:27:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they calibrate it 190 and 185\Nwhich is below the level of integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.40,1:27:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,so whatever they say is not so\Nit serves that positionality
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.04,1:27:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's very interesting to them\Nsee here's Uganda
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.04,1:27:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where the UN is\Nwhere all these things are happening
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.04,1:27:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and people want to turn our country over at 421\Nto the UN which calibrates about 195
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.04,1:27:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't make any sense to me at all\NI mean where are they with Haiti
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.04,1:28:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,where are they with Uganda\NI don't know what they do
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.04,1:28:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,they pass out parcels of food\Nso they're like an extension to me of the Red Cross
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.04,1:28:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and they do a lot of good\Nbut I wouldn't turn the rule of our country over to them
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.04,1:28:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so here you've got Africa\Nand here you've got Europe
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.17,1:28:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and here you've got Uganda\Nyou see you're around 50 or so
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.17,1:28:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the slaughtering of people there\Nso
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.65,1:28:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the calibrated levels then\Nshow a distribution somehow
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.65,1:28:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,now Europe has become secularized\Nwhere is Europe here
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.65,1:28:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened to Europe\N300 is up in here
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.03,1:28:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,see America\Nthe constitution of the United States
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.03,1:28:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates around 700\Nthe highest of any country in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.60,1:28:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the government itself calibrates extremely high\Nyou can criticize it
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.50,1:28:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's a matter of fact\Nif you calibrate it's the highest in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.50,1:28:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it is integrity by intent\Ndoesn't mean that it's perfect
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.50,1:29:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean that it's saintly\Nit's not saintly
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.50,1:29:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a government is not supposed to be saintly\Nit's supposed to protect its people
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.50,1:29:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so here we have\Nwhat happens with non-integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.17,1:29:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then is\Nthings go downhill
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.65,1:29:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but they only go downhill a little bit\Nif you stop at saintly
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.65,1:29:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,secularism then you're in\Nusually the high 200s or 300s
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.65,1:29:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that means\Nit doesn't mean you're not responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.65,1:29:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just that you eliminate God\Nfrom the equation
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.65,1:29:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you eliminate God from the equation\Nwhich is from a certain viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.65,1:29:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's fine with me\NI don't care if they do it
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.65,1:29:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't care about it\Nso whatever they want to do
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.84,1:29:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,alright let's move on to the next country\Nso here's the western hemisphere again
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.87,1:29:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why it recurred\Nwell let's go on
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.33,1:29:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we already saw the western hemisphere\Nhere's the other hemisphere
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.81,1:30:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,well because I thought these are easier to read\Nthe other was too full of data
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.81,1:30:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you see New Zealand and Australia\Nwould be good places to live
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.97,1:30:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't they\Nanything that's 400
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.97,1:30:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,355\Nall these higher calibrations
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.97,1:30:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if you want to retire\NI would retire to a higher calibration
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.00,1:30:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,here's where it's 40\Nit's not a good place to retire
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.22,1:30:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,there are the\Nwhat do you call those things
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.78,1:30:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,gorillas\Nand the gorillas calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.58,1:30:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,higher than the people there\NI would rather sit for breakfast
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.43,1:30:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with a mountain gorilla\Nthan the people who work there
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.13,1:30:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,alright we'll move on to the next\Nso we can't say
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.21,1:31:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,anything about it\Nexcept that
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.30,1:31:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,if we study the world\Nthis is what we find
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.34,1:31:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and North Africa we spend a little extra time on\Nbecause you know it's so much in the news
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.34,1:31:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Iraq and all such like\Nand
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.34,1:31:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple of the countries I was talking about\Nyou see are at the top
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.34,1:31:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can see they are not devoted to peace\Nand therefore all this
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.34,1:31:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation about it is conversation\Nand Iraq as a country
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.34,1:31:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was also far\Naway from peace
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.34,1:31:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Syria has come up since we did this map\Nif you recalibrate Syria
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.34,1:31:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see it came up\Nand Gaddafi has somehow gotten religion all of a sudden
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.34,1:31:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,for which we're all quite happy\Nto tell you the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.55,1:31:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Time magazine came out\Nso let's go to the next one
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.81,1:31:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in the trouble zones\Nwe're in North Africa
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.81,1:31:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,where we've experienced them\Nso we ask now what is the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.81,1:31:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you see because the human mind\Ncan't tell truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.90,1:32:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the human mind is impressionable\Nthe masters of rhetoric
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.74,1:32:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you know rhetoric political persuasiveness\Nhas been
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.77,1:32:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a formal study\Nwell in the year 350 BC
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.77,1:32:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so for the book I'm doing now\NI'm very sharp on it
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.06,1:32:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to reread Plato, Aristotle and Socrates\Nand the refutation
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.06,1:32:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of the argument\Nthe philosophic position of the sophist
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.06,1:32:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nwhat could be
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.66,1:32:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,saved from all of that\Nwould be some
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.66,1:32:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,rhetoric\Nthe good side of rhetoric
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.66,1:32:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you present truth in a way\Nthat is palatable to the audience
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.02,1:32:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,now\Ntruth is not always palatable
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.08,1:32:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to the audience\Nin fact truth is often
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.08,1:32:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the last thing people want to hear\Nso I warn people
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.14,1:32:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I warn people\Nif you're interested in truth
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.50,1:33:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,then you have to pull in\Npositionalities
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.06,1:33:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the name of the new book\NI'm forgetting what it is already
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.06,1:33:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's going to be truth versus fallacy\Ntruth versus fallacy
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.06,1:33:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you decide something like that\Nit's always
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.06,1:33:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,truth versus fallacy\Nwhat happened to the war
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.86,1:33:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,oh okay\Nwe were doing World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.86,1:33:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can take all the events\Nof any major thing in history
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.86,1:33:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,they say if you haven't learned from history\Nyou have to repeat it
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.86,1:33:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see mankind has repeated it\Nover and over again
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.86,1:33:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,so what is the lesson that we should have learned\Nso that this doesn't keep repeating itself
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.66,1:33:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we learned that\Npeace is the automatic consequence of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.66,1:33:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the automatic consequence of falsity\Nit's as simple as that
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.66,1:33:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,where truth prevails\Npeace prevails
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.21,1:33:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's an automatic consequence of truth\Nso peace is not something
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.37,1:34:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you can force on people\Nor we'll kill you
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.49,1:34:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see\Nbecause the Iraqi war is still somewhat
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.49,1:34:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionalized in people's minds\Nwe should probably stay away from it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.62,1:34:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and what we do\Nwe'll go back to my earlier life
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.62,1:34:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and see how did people calibrate\Nand how did a war
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.62,1:34:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the greatest war in history\Nkill more people than any other war
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.62,1:34:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,how could such a thing happen\Nso we put the calibrations
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.10,1:34:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we just calibrated people\Nand you see very interesting things
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.10,1:34:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you see Winston Churchill at 510\Nnow Winston Churchill
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.51,1:34:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,when he said\Nin England before World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.61,1:34:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that war is coming and you'd better get yourself\Nready for it
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.61,1:34:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,they thought\NHitler was a war monger
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.15,1:34:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so they threw him out\Nand they brought in a gentleman
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.15,1:34:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,who said he was going to bring peace in our times\Npeace in our times
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.18,1:35:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was Neville Chamberlain\Nso
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.76,1:35:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Churchill was a realist\Nhe says I don't like the idea of it
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.76,1:35:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but you know frankly folks\NHitler's going to take over
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.89,1:35:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'd better be prepared\Nhe was thrown out as a war monger
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.89,1:35:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and the pacifists who calibrated 145\Nas exempted by Neville Chamberlain
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.89,1:35:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,at 185\Nbecame friendly with Hitler
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.89,1:35:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,when Erwin Churchill's hand\Nthey signed a peace treaty
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.40,1:35:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they signed a peace treaty\Nanybody who signs a peace treaty
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.46,1:35:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with somebody who calibrates\Nlet's see
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.46,1:35:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,by the end of the war\NAdolf Hitler calibrated about 145
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.46,1:35:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so here you got somebody\Nwho's in denial
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.46,1:35:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,at 185 full of sophistry\Nall about peace and all that stuff
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.87,1:35:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're signing a contract\Nwith this guy here
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.61,1:35:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and so you've got\Nwhat you've got is
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.61,1:36:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,wishful thinking naivete\Noh if we're just nice to them
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.79,1:36:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll be nice to us\Nso damn
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.34,1:36:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,he'll be nice to us\Nhe won't torture people
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.34,1:36:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to death so slowly\Nright
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.75,1:36:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,oh so delusion\Nso that when the chips fell
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.18,1:36:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,then\Nthe war started
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.89,1:36:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and they had to pull Winston out\NWinston was at 510
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.88,1:36:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,wow\Nwell we did
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.88,1:36:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the energy of\Nwhen we spoke at Oxford
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.88,1:36:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we stopped off in Scotland\Nand did
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.88,1:36:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the Scottish Tattoo\Nwhich is a military musical
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.07,1:36:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,extravaganza\Nput on in front of the palace
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.42,1:36:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,once a year\Nand we heard 100 bagpipes
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.42,1:36:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,imagine 100 pipers\Nwalking across
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.42,1:37:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the sound of it just made the hair on the back of your head stand right up\Nand we said
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.90,1:37:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what is magical\Nthere's something different about the sound of bagpipes
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.44,1:37:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that has nothing to do with music\Nno
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.63,1:37:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the most dreaded sound\Nin the history of warfare
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.63,1:37:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is the sound of another army coming towards you\Nwith the background of the sound of bagpipes
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.63,1:37:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,more scary\Nthan the screams of the
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.73,1:37:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Viking warriors\Nmore terrifying than any
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.14,1:37:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,when you because there's an energy field\Nat 505
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.56,1:37:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,505\Nit's not hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.02,1:37:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,505\Nyou better make sure you've
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.28,1:37:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,signed your will\N505
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.82,1:37:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is death\N505
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.95,1:37:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you see is not just courage\Nso the average warrior
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.95,1:38:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,transcends fear\N505
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.02,1:38:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we've all walked into a hail of bullets\Nknowing
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.02,1:38:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's how you get over 200\Nthe one in childbirth does the same thing
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.02,1:38:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,she knows she's risking her life\Nmost women in history
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.43,1:38:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,died in childbirth\Nso by the act of heroism
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.14,1:38:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for others\Nfor the sacredness of life
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.20,1:38:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,she puts her life\Non the line
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.26,1:38:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and frankly she used to lose it often\Nshe lost it often
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.19,1:38:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In the family Bible I have at home, the man was often married three or four times,\Nand many of the children died.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.38,1:38:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So the man goes over 200 when he's willing to face death for some higher principle,\Nhonor, love of country, to defend the homeland.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.39,1:39:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,505 is something else.\N505 is valor.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.19,1:39:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Valor calibrates 505.\NIn valor, you're not trying to prove anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.09,1:39:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to prove that you're not subject to fear anymore.\NYou proved that long ago at Calibration 11-200.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.69,1:39:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, 505 is being what you are in the face of all that is,\Nthe courage to be exactly who you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.43,1:39:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's extremely powerful.\NSo you see Winston at 510 was the,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.01,1:39:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,hmm,\Nwas the spiritual strength of the bulldog.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.40,1:39:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The bulldog.\NRoosevelt very close to him at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.06,1:39:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,President Truman, God bless him, he inherited a terrible problem.\NHe had to decide about the nuclear bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.80,1:39:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody envied him.\NAnd that involves triage.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.08,1:40:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to kill 200,000 to save the life of 6 or 7 million or not?\NNobody likes to be faced.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.28,1:40:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Every triage, every physician faces it.\NI faced it many a time.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.89,1:40:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The life of the mother, the life of the child.\NSo triage then is, was the problem that Truman faced.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.93,1:40:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And happily, he was at 495, which nobody would have predicted.\NI remember my father's description of Truman as being a haberdasher from someplace.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.28,1:40:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God help us, he says.\NA haberdasher from Missouri or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.10,1:40:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,God help us.\NWell, when called upon,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.66,1:40:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy came up in Truman.\NAnd he did the impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.88,1:40:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,None of us would want his decision.\NIf he said no, 7 million people would have died.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.12,1:40:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,7 million because you had the moral cowardice not to say yes.\NIf you say yes, you're going to be vilified in history as having killed 200,000 people.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.10,1:41:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're either going to be attacked one way or the other.\NSo should it be for the death of 200,000 or the death of 7 million?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.60,1:41:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the estimated death...\NThe death rate if we invaded Japan was at least 7 million, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.63,1:41:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we have MacArthur and all these people.\NWe can see Wernher von Braun, Heisenberg, the U.S. military.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.87,1:41:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The concept of triage itself is not well understood in America.\NIt's understood very well in medicine.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.51,1:41:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Los Alamos, you can see what the intention of all these people were.\NInteresting, you see the kamikaze pilot.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.97,1:41:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the kamikaze pilot.\NYou see the kamikaze pilot.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.05,1:41:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The pilot was already an integrous warrior.\NSo was the Luftwaffe, integrous warrior.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.91,1:41:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't do it to prove anything.\NThey did it out of duty.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.81,1:41:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hirohito's right on the edge at 200.\NTojo's at 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.89,1:41:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And Yamamoto had a certain amount of wisdom\Nbecause right from the beginning he said,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.85,1:42:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,well, we're going to lose this war.\NYamamoto was not popular because he said,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.19,1:42:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to lose.\NHe saw that right from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.89,1:42:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We've awakened the sleeping giant.\NNow let's see what else is going on here.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.62,1:42:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Oppenheimer, you know,\Nthen there were double agents in Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.72,1:42:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You can look at pictures of people and calibrate\Nand tell who's going to be the double agent
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.16,1:42:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because their consciousness is out.\NSo they can disguise their appearance
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.80,1:42:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and what they do and what they say,\Nbut they cannot disguise their level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.10,1:42:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you want people to work on a secret project\Nthat puts all of mankind at risk,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.16,1:42:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you better calibrate their level of consciousness.\NA lot of them are going to sell out,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.08,1:42:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and a certain number of them do.\NThe Cambridge Five sold out.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.53,1:42:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were the intellectuals coming out of England.\NThe traders all calibrated 40 or 50.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.00,1:42:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the League of Nations wasn't doing much better\Nthan the current, what do they call it, UN thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.49,1:43:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The League of Nations didn't do anything to stop World War II\Nany more than...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.16,1:43:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the UN's doing much of anything now.\NPacifism, the attack on Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.60,1:43:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph Goebbels is very interesting\Nbecause we learn from history.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.08,1:43:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What Goebbels exploited was the naivete of the human mind.\NHe knew people can't tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.88,1:43:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you repeat falsehood often enough,\Npeople will believe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.68,1:43:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the position, then, that the human ego gets into.\NBecause it has a warped view, it repeats it many times
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.08,1:43:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and then becomes conditioned.\NWe see the London Blitz, Dr. Mengele, the Rosenbergs.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.69,1:43:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,People still worry about the Rosenbergs.\NAnd Lord Ha-Ha, I always got a kick out of calibrating him,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.85,1:43:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,was 50.\NLord Ha-Ha, I forget his real name,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.19,1:43:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but he was a defector that used to be on radio\Nwith pro-Nazi propaganda.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.27,1:44:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's World War II.\NYou see, if you do all the famous wars in history,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.24,1:44:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you learn incredibly important things.\NWhat's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.01,1:44:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Break what?\NWe're going to take a break.
